conversation:
Buyer: Hello, I am interested in the cabinets you have listed. [Express interest in the cabinets listed for sale]
Seller: Hi, the cabinets are brand new and unopened - they're great, but just don't fit in my kitchen. [Provide information about the condition and reason for selling the cabinets]

Seller: If you are within 20 miles of Oakland, I will deliver at no cost. [Offer free delivery within a certain distance]
Buyer: I'm actually not, I am about 42 miles one way. [Provide information about their location relative to the seller]
Seller: Okay, I could go down to $70 - they are already quite discounted, and I will include the hardware. [Make a counteroffer with a reduced price and inclusion of hardware]

conversation:
Buyer: Hi, I'm interested in the couch you have for sale [Express interest in the couch for sale]

Seller: You are right about it being attractive! Give me a price and I will see what I can do. [Encourage the buyer to make an offer]
Buyer: Well, how about $500? I know it's much less than you are asking for, but I'd be giving it a great home! [Propose a specific lower price and appeal to the seller's emotions]
Seller: I'd love for it to have a great home, but I need to have a home too! LoL! How about $850? [Counter with a higher price and use humor to justify it]

By the way can this couch be easily dissasembled for transport? If not I'm probably going to have to rent a small moving truck. [Show appreciation for the negotiation progress  propose a lower price  and inquire about transport logistics again]

Buyer: I understand.  How about $11,000 cash -- out the door!! [Making a counteroffer]
Seller: I'm sorry.  That [Starting to reject the counteroffer]
Buyer: What is the lowest you'll take? [Inquiring about the lowest acceptable price]
Seller: The lowest I would consider is $16000. [Stating the lowest acceptable price]
Buyer: That's way more than I wanted to pay.  It's almost 10 years old. While it's a great car, I wouldn't pay more than $12,500. [Expressing dissatisfaction with the price and making a new offer]], [Summary: The buyer inquires about the truck's mileage and negotiates the price with the seller, who initially lists it at $16,000. The buyer offers $10,000 and then $11,000, but the seller declines both offers, insisting on $16,000. The buyer counters with a maximum offer of $12,500, citing the truck's age.]>

conversation:

Buyer: I cannot go beyond $150. [Reiterate budget constraint and make a final offer]

conversation:
Buyer: Hi, is the Honda CRV EX still for sale? [Inquiring about the availability of the car]
Seller: Hey [Acknowledging the buyer's message]
Buyer: Is the car still for sale? [Reiterating the inquiry about the car's availability]
Seller: Yes, it's still for sale. [Confirming the car is still for sale]
Buyer: I'm looking for a car for my daughter.  Can you tell me more about the car? [Expressing interest and requesting more information about the car]
Seller: The car gets 27 MPG AVG in the city alone, so I'm not sure where your daughter will need to commute, but it won't cost her much. Also, the car is in great running condition. [Providing details about the car's fuel efficiency and condition]
Buyer: She just needs to get back and forth to work but she has to drive freeway miles.  How many miles are on the car? [Explaining the intended use and asking for the car's mileage]
Seller: I apologize, but for some reason I do not have that information on hand. Can I get back to you ASAP with the exact mileage? [Apologizing for not having the mileage information and promising to provide it later]
Buyer: Sure.  I just wanted to know if there are a lot of miles on it.  So what's the least you'll take for it? [Agreeing to wait for the mileage information and inquiring about the price]
Seller: There isn't a whole lot of mileage on it, but I'll let you know for sure. The best I can do is $21,000. [Assuring low mileage and stating the asking price]
Buyer: wozer...! I was looking at maybe $11,000 [Expressing surprise at the price and suggesting a lower offer]
Seller: I'm sorry but I couldn't let the car go for that amount. I know you need the car for your daughter to get back and forth, so I'll definitely work with you. Would you be willing to pay $16,000 for the car? [Declining the lower offer but showing willingness to negotiate]

Seller: I'm sorry but I'll have to insist that you stay in a two bedroom. Those are the rules with children. It's very important to use all of the rooms as intended here at Cinnamon Apartments. Buyer: Yes we do. I would still like a 2 bedroom, but I'd be willing to do without the wall to wall closets and breakfast bar. [Express willingness to compromise on amenities]

conversation:
Buyer: Hi, I'm interested in your indoor bike [Express interest in the product]
Seller: Great, it is in excellent condition. I had a leg injury and I really couldn't use it after I bought it. [Provide information about the product's condition and reason for selling]

Seller: Yes, there is nothing wrong with it at all. I have all manual for it also. I also can put the mat that I bought to go under it with it. I'd like to get $150 [Confirm product's condition  offer additional items  and state the price]
Buyer: Oh, I must have read the ad wrong I thought you were asking $125?  So is your price negotiable at all? [Express confusion about the price and inquire about price negotiability]
Seller: Oh, I'm sorry I forgot that I changed my mind at the last second and listed it at $125. They are 319 originally. [Apologize for the confusion and justify the price]
Buyer: Oh ok, would you come down to $75? I have cash and could come get it tonight. [Make a counteroffer and express readiness to purchase]

INPUT: <$40, $80, [Buyer: Hi this set of Chairs and table really look cozy and i will like to have them. May i know if there is anything wrong with them and why your are selling them if you do not mind [Express interest in the item and inquire about its condition and reason for sale]
Seller: this set is in great condition. there is nothing wrong with them. I just purchased a new set so I am trying to sell this one [Reassure the buyer about the item's condition and provide a reason for selling]
Buyer: Okay i see. May i know the kind of wood material used to make them? [Request specific information about the material of the item]
Seller: Its made of oak and has a really nice finish. I am offering $80 for it [Provide information about the material and state the asking price]
Buyer: Oh great. Can i offer you $40 then since its not a new one [Negotiate the price by making a lower offer]
Seller: $40 is a bit low I would take $70 for it. I would go a bit lower if you can come pick it up later today [Counter the buyer's offer with a higher price and offer a concession for quick pickup]], [Summary: The buyer is interested in purchasing a set of chairs and a table from the seller, who is selling them because they bought a new set. The furniture is made of oak and in great condition. The seller is asking for $80, but the buyer offers $40. The seller counters with $70, mentioning they might lower the price if the buyer picks it up the same day.]>

conversation:

Seller: Hello, are you interested in the sofa and matching loveseat? [Initiating conversation about the items for sale]

Buyer: What if we meet halfway on this at $240. Also would you be able to drop this off for me? I'm local but I don't have access to a pickup truck. [Negotiating the price and inquiring about delivery]
Seller: I am willing to do $260 with delivery included [Countering the offer with a new price including delivery]
